HEADWORD: Antiseptical
<hw>An`ti*sep"tic*al</hw>
<pr>(<?/)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>a.</pos> <def>Counteracting or preventing
putrefaction, or a putrescent tendency in the system;
antiputrefactive.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Antiseptic surgery</b></col>, <cd>that system of surgical
practice which insists upon a systematic use of antiseptics in the
performance of operations and the dressing of wounds.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Antiseptic</ent>⟦br⟧
